SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 10
By Walley
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Dr. Richard E. Berryman
of Bolivar.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Dr. Richard E. Berryman; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Berryman was an exemplary public servant and consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born in Hardeman County to Henry Earl Berryman and Hazel Keller
Berryman, Dr. Berryman was a highly respected member of his community and graduated from
Bolivar Central High School as the valedictorian of his class; and
WHEREAS, after graduating, Dr. Berryman attended the University of Tennessee at
Martin for his Bachelor of Science degree and then the University of Tennessee College of
Dentistry for his Doctor of Dental Surgery degree; and
WHEREAS, under the mentorship of Dr. Harold Fitts, he began his career in dentistry in
1968 and then opened his own practice in 1971, dedicating over fifty-six years of his life to the
field of dentistry; and
WHEREAS, in all of his endeavors, Dr. Berryman earned the respect of his colleagues,
community, and patients alike for the superior quality of his work; and
WHEREAS, he was an active and devout member of Gideons International and Bolivar
First Baptist Church, where he served as a deacon and Sunday School teacher faithfully for
many years; and
